<2ND_LINE>PM-Secret Client,0335</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Million-Dollar Reward Offered For Identity of Secret Client</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PALM BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The parents of a man killed by a
hit-and-run driver have offered a $1 million reward and appealed to
a national television audience for information that might reveal
the driver's identity.
   Mark Baltes was struck by a white Buick on an oceanside drive
here and dragged 60 feet to his death more than 2{ years ago.
   Attorney Barry Krischer says the driver approached him for
counsel the day after the accident, but he has won court permission
to keep the name a secret on the grounds of attorney-client
confidentiality.
   Krischer again refused to identify the driver when interviewed
on CBS-TV's ``60 Minutes,'' broadcast Sunday night.
   A tearful Mildred Baltes also appeared on the show and said she
was determined to find the driver so she can put her son's tragedy
behind her.
   Mrs. Baltes and her ex-husband, Joseph Baltes, say they must win
a $6 million lawsuit against the driver before they can pay off any
reward money.
   That suit was filed in February over the March 9, 1986,
accident. It is pending in Palm Beach County Circuit Court while
state and private investigators continue trying to track down the
driver.
   On Oct. 12, Circuit Judge Timothy Poulton said Krischer did not
have to reveal the driver's name because it is protected by
attorney-client privilege.
   ``This criminal is out there laughing at the system, hiding
behind the attorney-client privilege,'' says Joseph Farish,
attorney for Baltes' family. He devised the reward plan, announced
on Friday, ``in order to make incentive for someone to come forward
and expedite this mystery.''
   Farish conceded that if someone comes forward with information
leading to the driver's identity, the tipster would have to wait
for a favorable jury verdict in the lawsuit.
   Richard Lubin, who represents Krischer, said he is indifferent
to Farish's tactics, as long as Farish does not trample on the
judge's ruling.
</TEXT>
