<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Zaire-Libya,0080</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Libya, Zaire Renew Diplomatic Relations</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KINSHASA, Zaire (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Zaire and Libya have renewed diplomatic
relations broken after Kinshasa established ties with Israel in
1982.
   Relations further deteriorated when President Mobutu Sese Seko
provided military assistance to Chad, which was engaged in a war
with neighboring Libya. Libyan leader Col. Moammar Gadhafi
announced Oct. 3 that his country was normalizing relations with
Chad. He also said he wished to renew cooperation with other
African countries.
</TEXT>
