<HEAD>Death Toll From Weekend Fire Now 12</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four people who were critically burned
in a weekend fire at an illegal plastics factory died Monday,
raising the death toll 12, the Press Trust of India news agency
reported.
   The fire swept through the factory Saturday, injuring 45 people.
At least 11 people remained in critical condition with severe
burns, the agency said.
   The fire at the plant, which was operating without a license,
was started by an exploding gas cylinder, police said.
