<HEAD>Former Reporter Meredith S. Buel Dead At 65</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Meredith S. Buel, a special assistant to the
chairman of the National Mediation Board and former reporter and
editor for the Washington Evening Star, died here Monday of cancer.
He was 65.
   Buel had been with the Mediation Board, which regulates labor
relations in the railroad and airline industries, as its chief
spokesman for 10 years. Prior to that he was public relations
director for the American Institute of Merchant Shipping.
   He had been a reporter and editor for the now-defunct Washington
Evening Star from 1948 to 1958. Buel is survived by his wife,
Joyce; a son, Meredith S. Buel Jr., and a daughter, Marianne.
   Robin Stein, a spokeswoman for the board, said funeral
arrangements were incomplete.
