<1ST_LINE>r a AM-PresidentBiographies     10-24 0210</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-President Biographies,0216</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dell Ready To Publish, No Matter Who Wins</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dell Publishing is ready to print the biography
of the 41st president of the United States _ whoever he may be.
   The publishing house has prepared biographies, intended for an
audience of children, of both Massachusetts Gov. Michael Dukakis
and Vice President George Bush, and is now waiting for the election
to write the final chapter.
   ``That task will be completed on Nov. 9. Needless to say, there
will be a happy ending for the book that gets published,'' said
Michelle Poploff, executive editor at Dell.
   The book is to be published shortly before Inauguration Day, and
will concentrate on the winner's childhood years.
   Biographers Mark Sufrin and Lynn Beach started following the
field of candidates last spring and got down to serious research
and writing when the nominees were selected.
   Two nearly identical covers have already been printed, each
bearing a color photograph of the man. The oath of office is
printed on each cover, with the appropriate name inserted.
   The loser's biography is targeted for the ash heap of history.
   ``There can be only one president of the United States and only
one presidential biography,'' said Poploff. ``May the best
manuscript win.''
</TEXT>
