<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Egg Output, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0698,60</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Hens Working Harder</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS final graf to CORRECT average number of eggs per hen in
September 1987 to 2,024, sted 2,204</NOTE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The nation's hens shelled out an estimated
5.55 billion eggs last month, down 2 percent from September 1987,
the Agriculture Department said Monday.
   But there were 3 percent fewer hens in laying flocks in
September _ an estimated average of 272 million birds during the
month, compared with 281 million a year ago, the department said in
its monthly report.
   Thus, each hen worked harder, averaging 2,037 eggs per 100
layers, up from 2,024 eggs in September 1987, the report said.
</TEXT>
