<2ND_LINE>AM-People-Nielsen,0224</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Publicist: Nielsen to Have Surgery; Condition Not Life Threatening</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHOENIX (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actress Brigitte Nielsen will undergo laser
surgery for an undisclosed procedure this week, but her condition
is not life-threatening, her publicist said Monday.
   The New York Times quoted Nielsen as saying last week that she
had cancer of the uterus and planned to enter an unspecified
Arizona hospital Monday for a biopsy. However, friends close to her
fiance, former New York Jets defensive end Mark Gastineau, have
said it's unlikely Nielsen is gravely ill.
   Publicist Joel Brokaw said from Los Angeles that he spoke with
Nielsen late Monday afternoon, while she was still with her doctor.
   Brokaw said she did not tell him what the condition was, that
she said it was not life-threatening, but it could rapidly become
so if not taken care of promptly.
   He said he had no information on the planned surgery.
   Gastineau last week announced he was quitting football because
he wanted to help Nielsen through her illness. He and Nielsen last
week flew to Arizona, where his family lives.
   Gastineau's estranged wife said Sunday she didn't think her
husband was quitting football because of Nielsen's illness, and the
New York and Long Island newspaper Newsday quoted two friends of
Gastineau as saying Nielsen did not have cancer.
</TEXT>
