<HEAD>London Stocks Lower At Midday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices fell Monday as players began the week
in a nervous mood about higher interest rates and Thursday's
British trade report for September.
   Prices also drifted lower in the absence of fresh news affecting
speculative situations, a major force giving the market its recent
buoyancy.
   ``The market needs a constant supply of new bid stories to keep
prices on the boil,'' said one equity salesman.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index was down 6.4
points, or 0.3 percent, at 1,852.9 at midday.
   Volume was light, as 289.5 million shares changed hands,
compared with 311.7 million shares at the same time Friday.
</TEXT>
