<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-MartinMarietta     10-24 0197</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Martin Marietta,0204</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Posts Profit Jump in 3rd Qtr</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BETHESDA, Md. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Martin Marietta Corp. said Monday its
third-quarter earnings surged nearly fourfold, mainly because of a
gain on the sale of its interest in a British-based computer
services company.
   The aerospace and defense company reported earnings of $202.8
million, or $3.82 per share, for the three months ended Sept. 30
compared with a profit of $55.6 million, or $1.02 per share, a year
earlier.
   The latest results include a onetime after-tax gain of $135.7
million, or $2.55 per share, from the sale of the company's 68.3
percent interest in Hoskyns Group PLC, a London-based computer
services concern.
   Without the gain, the company said its earnings per share for
the quarter would have risen 23 percent from a year ago.
   Sales for the quarter rose 10.6 percent to $1.46 billion from
$1.32 billion from the same period in 1987.
   For the first nine months, earnings nearly doubled to $335.2
million, or $6.30 per share, compared with $171.3 million, or $3.13
per share, in the same period a year ago. Sales for the nine months
rose 9.1 percent to $4.20 billion from $3.85 billion in 1987.
</TEXT>
