prices. UAL rose 1[ to 98\; NWA 1\ to 53\; Delta Air Lines } to
51[, and AMR { to 50{.
   As measured by Wilshire Associates' index of more than 5,000
actively traded stocks, the market lost $10.13 billion, or 0.36
percent, in value from its Friday close.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks
dropped .57 to 158.85.
   Standard & Poor's industrial index fell 1.36 to 325.48, and
S&P's 500-stock composite index was down 1.38 at 282.28.
