<1ST_LINE>r f BC-WeeklySteel     10-24 0145</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Weekly Steel,0146</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Steel Output Rose 3.3 Percent in Week</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Steel production rose to 1.856 million tons in
the week ended Oct. 22, an increase of 3.3 percent from the
previous week's 1.797 million tons, the American Iron and Steel
Institute reported Monday.
   The industry's production amounted to 86.6 percent of capacity
during the week, compared with 83.8 percent in the previous week.
   Estimated figures for the year to date showed production at
80.945 million net tons, an increase of 16.1 percent from the
69.725 million net tons in the previous year.
   Production so far this year used 89.4 percent of capacity,
compared with 77.0 percent a year earlier.
   Net tonnage by district for the week ended Oct. 22: Northeast
Coast, 276,000; Pittsburgh, 189,000; Youngstown, 96,000; Lake Erie,
150,000; Detroit, 161,000; Chicago, 471,000; Midwest, 190,000;
Southern, 229,000; and Western, 94,000.
</TEXT>
